Centre Jour is an instant classic. The control, audio, and art of the game works together to completely pull you into the game. Just when I was starting to think I've done it all with physics puzzlers, I am treated to a unique spin on the genre that feels familiar with the world of too like atmosphere. Instead of interacting with a character in the game, you more or less alter the world and interact with the background to gather up to three lights and reach a large glowing light to complete the level. It's easy enough to beat if you don't care to get three stars in each level, but provides a decent amount of challenge to a casual gamer to complete 3 stars on each one. I'm happy to support developers that work as hard as they did to bring us such a polished game.
